Habit formation is the process by which a behavior becomes progressively more automatic through repetition. The more you repeat an activity, the more the structure of your brain changes to become efficient at that activity. Neuroscientists call this longterm potentiation, which refers to the strengthening of connections between neurons in the brain based on recent patterns of activity. With each repetition, celltocell signaling improves and the neural connections tighten.
